{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"## S4a implemented + verified LIVE on Gerrit — 2026-06-30 (commit 87bde6fe0)\n\n**AC verification (all live):**\n- AC1 — Bot identity: account `rebar-review-bot` (id 1000002) in the built-in `Service Users` group (SERVICE_USER), created via `gerrit create-account` over SSH (admin key); HTTP token generated, rotated (`set-account --delete-token default` then `--http-password`) and stored in SSM `/rebar/prod/gerrit-bot-token`. service-user.sh is idempotent (create-or-rotate; only an \"already exists\" error falls through to rotate — real errors fail fast).\n- AC2 — IAM: the instance role's SSM read is scoped to `parameter/rebar/prod/*` (S1, no Resource:*); covers the bot token path. iam_s4a.tf is a doc anchor (no new grant needed, no duplicate role).\n- AC3 — Plugins: `webhooks` is bundled+ENABLED in the 3.14.1 image; `events-log` installed from a pinned, sha256-verified jar (46ef4f87…, 3.14.1) and is ENABLED (a rebuild reinstalls byte-identical). Provenance in infra/gerrit/plugins/README.md.\n- AC4 — webhooks.config is a committed TEMPLATE (no secret); service-user.sh renders it with the SSM token (awk substitution) and SURGICALLY pushes ONLY webhooks.config to rebar refs/meta/config. Verified S3's config is preserved (LLM-Review label still present post-push).\n- AC5 — Webhook delivery + network control: the `webhooks` remote POSTs `patchset-created` to the receiver. PROVEN live — pushing a test change made the receiver log `POST /webhook?token=… → 202 Accepted` from `172.21.0.3` (the gerrit container, INTERNAL compose network). Delivery is internal (URL = http://review-bot:8000/webhook), never traversing public nginx. Network-ACL control verified: an external `curl http://52.3.128.230:8000/` TIMES OUT (port 8000 loopback-bound + not in the SG). Token in URL is a secondary control (ADR-0014); S4b validates it receiver-side.\n- AC6 — events-log queryable: `GET /a/plugins/events-log/events/` (NOTE: trailing slash REQUIRED — without it 404s) returns recent events (16 events incl. ref-updated/patchset-created), authenticated as the bot. **S4b's reconciler must use the trailing-slash path.**\n- Bonus AC: the bot HTTP token authenticates BOTH Gerrit REST `/a/` (GET /a/accounts/self → 200) AND git-over-HTTPS clone (`git clone https://rebar-review-bot:<token>@host/a/rebar` → OK) — the receiver's read path covers both.\n\n**Notes for S4b:** (a) events-log query needs the trailing slash `/events/`; (b) the inbound webhook token = the SSM bot token (same secret); (c) the receiver currently returns 202 to any POST (skeleton) — S4b adds token validation + the review/vote logic; (d) any token rotation via service-user.sh requires a Gerrit restart to reload webhooks.config.\n\n**Code review (subagent):** VERDICT PASS (no blockers). Folded the one substantive NIT: service-user.sh now gates the create→rotate fallback on the \"already exists\" error (real create failures fail fast, not silently misclassified)."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782790626932526001,"uuid":"aaed947a-239f-414d-b2ff-5860bd9e22bf"}